## Procedure of data modification  
1.  The training and the test sets were merged into one data set.  
2.  The measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement were extracted, by using grep().  
3.  The numbers indicating activity names were replaced with the actual names.  
4.  In order to change the feature (variable) names into the descriptive ones, the symbols included in the names ("-", "()") were deleted and the original variable names in lowercase ("mean" and "std") were replaced with the ones beginning with the capital letters ("Mean" and "Std"), by using gsub().  
5.   The average of each variable for each activity and each subject was calculated, by using melt() and acast(). Then a second independent tidy data set (“tidydata.csv”) was created.


